{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There are no steps needed to migrate to 1.19 of the Composable Architecture, but there are a number","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of changes and improvements that have been made to the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Store","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that one should be aware of.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Store internals rewrite","anchor":"Store-internals-rewrite"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The store’s internals have been rewritten to improved performance and to pave the way for future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"features. While this should not be a breaking change, with any rewrite it is important to thoroughly"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"test your application after upgrading.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"StateObject compatibility","level":2,"anchor":"StateObject-compatibility","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"text":" allow a view to own a value or object over time, ensuring that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"when a parent view is recomputed, the view-local state isn’t recreated from scratch.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"One important difference between ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"type":"text","text":" is that "},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"eager, while ","type":"text"},{"code":"@StateObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"‘s is lazy. Because of this, if you initialize a root "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Store"},{"text":" to be held","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", stores will be initialized (and immediately discarded) whenever the parent view’s body","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is computed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To avoid the creation of these stores, one can now assign the store to a ","type":"text"},{"code":"@StateObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", instead:"}]},{"code":["struct FeatureView: View {","  @StateObject var store: StoreOf<Feature>","","  init() {","    _store = StateObject(","      \/\/ This expression is only evaluated the first time the parent view is computed.","      wrappedValue: Store(initialState: Feature.State()) {","        Feature()","      }","    )","  }","","  var body: some View { \/* ... *\/ }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The store’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ObservableObject"},{"text":" conformance does not have any impact on the actual","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"observability of the store. You should continue to rely on the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/ObservableState()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" macro for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"observation.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"title":"Migrating to 1.19","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"article","sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationG